Today marks the 15th anniversary of the al-Qaeda terrorist attacks on the U.S. Embassies in Nairobi, Kenya, and Dar es Salaam, Tanzania. The attacks resulted in the deaths of twelve Americans and over 200 Africans, with more than 5,000 wounded. The President pays tribute to those who lost their lives and meets with survivors during a memorial event. The United States is committed to protecting its citizens serving overseas and working with partners to combat violent extremism in East Africa and globally. Efforts to bring terrorists to justice and prevent future attacks will continue. The President extends condolences to the families affected by the 1998 attack and honors their memory by striving for a safer and more prosperous world.